{# Per-context liveness alerts, one per entry in netdata_contexts.
   $last_collected_t is a first-class netdata field on every chart, so
   we can alert on it directly without scraping /api/v2/contexts and
   re-exposing the result as a Prometheus gauge. The configured-but-
   never-instantiated case (where the named context never appears in
   the chart registry at all, so a template with `on: <missing>` silently
   drops) is covered by netdata_presence.chart.sh + netdata_presence_alerts.conf.

   Do NOT add per-instance contexts here. apps.plugin emits one chart
   per app/user/usergroup under `app.cpu_utilization`,
   `user.cpu_utilization`, `usergroup.cpu_utilization`, etc., so a
   template with `on: app.cpu_utilization` fans out to ~50 alerts --
   one per group. Transient groups (postdrop, _apt, build,
   packagemanager, container subuids that map to ephemeral pids) stop
   updating the moment no matching processes are running, so their
   $last_collected_t goes stale and the alert fires forever. Only
   list contexts that resolve to a single always-on chart. apps.plugin
   liveness as a whole is covered by netdata.service's systemd unit
   alerts in systemdunits.conf -- if it crashes, the parent restarts
   it, so silent apps-only failures are not in scope here. #}
{% for name, ctx in netdata_contexts.items() %}
template: liveness_{{ name }}
      on: {{ ctx }}
    calc: $now - $last_collected_t
   every: 60s
    crit: $this > (60)
   delay: up 5m
 summary: Context {{ name }} ({{ ctx }}) is stale
    info: netdata has not collected {{ ctx }} for over 60s
      to: sysadmin

{% endfor %}
{# Per-collector staleness + iteration-failure alerts. Fans out to every
   netdata.go_d_<plugin>_<job>_data_collection_status chart without
   per-collector enumeration; netdata_presence_alerts.conf covers the
   configured-but-never-instantiated gap separately. #}
template: collector_stale
      on: netdata.plugin_data_collection_status
    calc: $now - $last_collected_t
   every: 60s
    crit: $this > (60)
   delay: up 5m
 summary: Collector ${chart} has stopped reporting
    info: A go.d collector has not run a data collection iteration in over 60s
      to: sysadmin

template: collector_failing
      on: netdata.plugin_data_collection_status
  lookup: max -5m of failed
   every: 60s
    crit: $this > (0)
   delay: down 5m
 summary: Collector ${chart} reported a failed iteration
    info: A go.d collector reported a failed data-collection iteration in the last 5m
      to: sysadmin
